23/08/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Another round of heavy rain was reported Monday (22 August) evening in Bulgaria, especially in the northern district of Montana. Lightning in the village of Murchavo killed a 62-year-old man. Elsewhere, rescue teams managed to save ten people, including four children, from drowning. The finance ministry says it will ask the EU for more flood-related assistance. 
Heavy rains also lashed neighbouring Turkey Monday. The governor of the northeast province of Rize says four people -- two women and two children -- died in a landslide in the village of Cayirduzu. (bTV, BNR - 23/08/05; NTV - 22/08/05) 
